  "text": "Since the model is linear, the intensity of the flow increases monotonically as the forcing increases. The in-phase component 1 decreases monotonically as dissipation and diffusion increase, while the out-of-phase component 2 initially increases as dissipation and diffusion increase, to decrease monotonically for large values of dissipation and diffusion (equations (33) and (34) of Appendix A1). The flow components 1 and 1 are lag ϭ /. The values of the coefficients a, b, and c in (12) and (13) are given in (35) of the Appendix. The last formulas in (12) and (13) hold when the diffusion is small. We recall that a fully developed sea breeze has a horizontal scale of two Rossby radius, k Ϸ 1/R 0 , and a vertical scale of double the CBL depth, Ϸ 1/h, in (12) and in (13) [CITATION_1] , which gives a time",
